<img width="303" height="395" class="wp-image-1064966" style="width: 600px;" src="https://cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/Screen-Shot-2018-09-28-at-08.25.48.png" alt="Adeleke, APC, PDP" srcset="https://cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/Screen-Shot-2018-09-28-at-08.25.48.png?width=303&amp;auto_optimize=medium 303w, https://cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/Screen-Shot-2018-09-28-at-08.25.48-230x300.png?width=230&amp;auto_optimize=medium 230w, https://cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/Screen-Shot-2018-09-28-at-08.25.48-44x58.png?width=44&amp;auto_optimize=medium 44w, https://cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/Screen-Shot-2018-09-28-at-08.25.48-149x194.png?width=149&amp;auto_optimize=medium 149w, https://cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/Screen-Shot-2018-09-28-at-08.25.48-100x130.png?width=100&amp;auto_optimize=medium 100w" sizes="(max-width: 303px) 100vw, 303px" />By Abdulmumin Murtala, Kano The North West Zonal Vice Chairman of the People’s Democratic Party (PDP) Sen Bello Hayatu Gwarzo has described the victory of the Party in the recently concluded governorship election in Osun State as a light for the party. He made the statement in Kano while issuing a congratulatory message to Sen Ademola Adeleke on behalf of the PDP family in the North West Zone. Gwarzo further described Adeleke as dogged adding that he fought for his stolen mandate of the People’s Democratic Party. “Sen Adeleke is a leader that demonstrated leadership by working tirelessly for the party. He is someone that the people of Osun want at this crucial moment where things have deteriorated in all sectors in the state. “His victory is a light for our party and an indicator that PDP will emerge victorious in the 2023 poll. “As we are prepare for the 2023 election, Nigerians should put it at the back of their mind that PDP is ready to reposition this country and make their lives better. “It’s obvious that the current predicament the APC led government has inflicted on us is not only a failure of leadership but lack of strategy and preparedness. They came unprepared but our party is prepared” he declared.    Former Nigerian Vice President and Peoples Democratic Party, PDP’s presidential candidate, Alhaji Atiku Abubakar and other PDP bigwigs have congratulated Osun Governor-elect, Senator Ademola Adeleke over his election victory at the just concluded Osun governorship poll. In "Osun election" Osun: PDP governors’ forum congratulates Adeleke In "Osun election" Member, Board of Trustee (BOT) of the Peoples Democratic Party, PDP, Senator Jim Nwobodo has described the electoral victory of Senator Ademola Adeleke of Osun State as a preamble to the prostective fortunes of the PDP in next year's general elections. In "News"